an intermediary, which in our case represented OEM customers. In the with-and-without method, the fair value was measured by the difference
between the present values of the cash flows with and without the existing customers in place over the period of time necessary to reacquire the
customers. In both instances, the economic useful life was determined based on historical customer turnover rates.
