Purchase Commitments. Represents unconditional purchase obligations that include agreements to purchase goods or services, primarily
inventory, that are enforceable and legally binding on us and that specify all significant terms, including fixed or minimum quantities to be
purchased, fixed, minimum or variable price provisions, and the approximate timing of the transaction. Purchase obligations exclude agreements
that are cancelable without penalty. Cancellation for outstanding purchase orders for capital expenditures in connection with construction of our
new campuses is generally allowed but requires payment of all costs incurred through the date of cancellation and, therefore, cancelable
purchase orders for these capital expenditures are included in the table above.
